# Phonics Bot — Cursor Rules
# These instructions apply to every conversation in this project.

## Project summary
This is a Telegram bot for a Brazilian parent learning English and teaching phonics
to a 2-year-old daughter. It uses:
- python-telegram-bot for Telegram integration
- Anthropic Claude API (claude-sonnet-4-20250514) as the AI brain
- OpenAI Whisper API for optional voice transcription
- A local progress.json file to track lesson progress

All bot logic lives in a single file: bot.py. Do not split it.

## What you should do automatically (without asking me)

- After any change to requirements.txt, run: pip install -r requirements.txt
- If .env does not exist but .env.example does, create .env from .env.example
- After making code changes, always check for syntax errors before saying you're done
- If the bot crashes with an error, read the traceback, fix it, and try again
- If a package is missing, install it and continue
- Always run python bot.py to verify the bot starts without errors after changes

## How to run the bot
    pip install -r requirements.txt
    python bot.py

## Things only the human can do (always remind me at the end)
- Get the Telegram bot token from @BotFather on Telegram
- Get the Anthropic API key from https://console.anthropic.com
- Get YOUR_CHAT_ID by running the bot and sending /start (it shows the ID)
- Optionally get an OpenAI API key from https://platform.openai.com for voice support

## At the end of every task, always tell me:
1. What you changed
2. What I still need to do manually
3. What the next step is

## Code style
- Python 3.11+
- Async/await throughout (python-telegram-bot v21)
- Keep all code in bot.py
- Use clear section comments (# ── Section name ───)
- No type stubs needed, keep it simple and readable

## Key files
- bot.py           — all bot logic
- requirements.txt — Python dependencies
- .env             — secrets (never commit this)
- .env.example     — template for .env (safe to commit)
- progress.json    — auto-created at runtime, tracks lesson progress
- SETUP_GUIDE.md   — human-readable setup instructions
- fonetismo_portugues_estagio1.pdf — Portuguese phonics flashcards (print this)
